    fix(production): serialize WO genealogy allocation and reject mixed UoM
    
    WO-level advisory lock prevents concurrent different-output-type registrations
    from collectively exceeding parent net consumption; mixed parent-consumption UoMs
    are rejected before allocation instead of summed under min(uom).
    
